m of a super Earth/mini Neptune. Water-dominated\natmospheres only exist for carbon to oxygen ratios much lower than the solar\nratio, suggesting that this kind of atmospheres could be rare.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 5 Jan 2014 22:30:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
